    "DLTraditional ML algorithms depend on extracting manual features, which has a great influence on the algorithm performance.",
    "However, extracting features is often based on the human experience and should be investigated on a case by case basis, thus lacking a unified approach.",
    "Fortunately, DL leverages the DNN for the automatic feature extraction and pattern recognition, overcoming the challenges of manual feature extraction [199].",
    "Typical DNNs include the feedforward neural network (FNN) [200], convolutional neural network (CNN) [201,202], and recurrent neural network (RNN) [203,204], which are described as below.",
